args: I will lay down all that I am in order to\nsee this relationship made whole!

With that, Brunhilda resolved to become human
in both body and mind. Afterward, she spent
all her days at the side of her beloved as
both his partner and a fellow traveler.
Good morning, darling! I made breakfast.\nIt's a hearty porridge, so eat up.
Ahhh, this is good. Warms me up\nfrom the inside out.
Oh, but I am delighted to hear that!\nA girl I met at the adventurers' guild\ntaught me the recipe.
The secret ingredient is LOVE!\n...Well, that and brown sugar.\nAnyway, there's plenty, so eat up!
So according to our map,\nthe town is this way.
I see, thanks. I can always count on\nyour directions.
I travel a lot easier now thanks to you.
Maybe, but you're the one who's always\nkeeping me safe from fiends!
(I've never known happiness like this!\nAh, but it is a joy to mutually support\nthe one who you love most.)
(THIS is what being a human married\ncouple is like! THIS is happiness!)
(I've lost my pride as a dragon,\nbut I've gained something more\nvaluable in exchange!)
(This one looks strong—maybe the\nstrongest we've yet faced in this world.)
(But my darling is amazing, so I'm sure\nthere's nothing to worry about!)
Fall back, Mym! This one's too much for ya!
You make this look easy, my love!
Ugh! I can't see! Where is he?!
That was Mym! She couldn't have...\nMym! MYYYYYYM!
(One hit? One lousy hit? Again I bemoan\nthese pathetic human fleshbags!)
I'm fine! But it's 'cause of me that you...
Hush. So long as you're all right...\nthat's all I care about...
Now fight, darling! Defeat that fiend!
I can't. I can't fight anymore.
You're my reason for livin'. Without ya...
(No! If he doesn't fight back, he'll...)
(I need to do something, but this\nstupid body just...won't...move!)
(Is this really how it ends for us?)
(Hmm... Well, perhaps that's not all bad.)
(Rather than one of us living alone,\nthe two of us can pass on together.)
(That's a very human way to go,\nI would imagine.)
(But am I truly all right with that?)
(Can I sit back and just watch him die?)
(...No! My love will not allow it!)
(Now MOVE, you useless body!\nShow some guts for once and MOVE!)
(The strong, proud Flamewyrm can't die\nto something so mean as THIS!)
(What? Th-this is the power of a dragon...\nBut I'm supposed to be human now!)
(Ah! The outfit was ripped when that\nfiend attacked me! Perhaps that's it?)
(Oh, who cares about the reason?\nThere's only one thing that matters now!)
I will protect the one I love!
I won't let you harm him! Even if my life\nis forfeit, I won't let my love burn out!
*pant* *pant* THAT is what happens when\nyou make the Flamewyrm mad!
Flamewyrm? Mym, what the hell\njust happened?!
I'm sorry for keeping this from you,\ndarling, but I'm actually a dragon.
Oh dear. It looks like it's time for me\nto say farewell to this world.
Mym, wait! Where are you going?!
I figured this would happen when I\nreclaimed my dragon power.
But I didn't have another option.

The thought of losing all the happiness
I'd gained as a human was frightening,
but the thought of watching the man
I love die was far, far worse.
Mym, no! Don't leave me! Myyyyym!
No regrets, now. After all, I was able to\nsay my goodbyes while you yet lived.
Farewell, my other darling.\nIt was wonderful to be with you.
It feels like ages since I\nwas last in the Halidom.
And now that I'm back, all of my\nadventures feel like a dream.
But I still have this outfit, so it doesn't\nhave to remain a distant memory.
If I was to wear it and wish again,\nI could experience other worlds anew.
No. I am finished with that.
I am a dragon to the core. I fell in love\nprecisely BECAUSE I am a dragon.
No matter the odds against me or how\nmad the dream, I will continue on the\npath of a dragon who loves a human.
But rather than indulging in dreams,\nI'm going to make my dream a reality!

Happy Halloween, my darling.
Despite how painful it can be,
I won't try to be anything but
myself, dragon and all.
